data.chText: （车辆或机器的）操纵杆，控制杆
data.enText: a handle used to operate a vehicle or piece of machinery

data.chText: 把操纵杆向你身体一侧拉动以调节速度。
data.enText: Pull the lever towards you to adjust the speed.
a long piece of wood, metal, etc. used for lifting or opening sth by sb placing one end of it under an object and pushing down on the other end
an action that is used to put pressure on sb to do sth they do not want to do

data.chText: 实施制裁的威胁是我们争取和平最有力的施压手段。
data.enText: The threat of sanctions is our most powerful lever for peace.
to move sth with a lever
I levered the lid off the pot with a knife.
They managed to lever the door open.

simple_means.memory_skill: lev 举起 + er 表物 → 举起〔重物〕的物 → 杠杆

means: (车辆或机器的)操纵杆，控制杆

tr: a rigid bar pivoted about a fulcrum
a flat metal tumbler in a lever lock
a simple machine that gives a mechanical advantage when given a fulcrum
to move or force, especially in an effort to get something open
example: The burglar jimmied the lock": "Raccoons managed to pry the lid off the garbage pail

value.def: A lever is a handle or bar that is attached to a piece of machinery and which you push or pull in order to operate the machinery.

example.ex: Push the tiny lever on the lock...
The taps have a lever to control the mix of hot and cold water.
example.tran: 水阀上有一个手柄控制冷热水。

value.def: A lever is a long bar, one end of which is placed under a heavy object so that when you press down on the other end you can move the object.
If you lever something in a particular direction, you move it there, especially by using a lot of effort.

example.ex: Neighbours eventually levered open the door with a crowbar...
example.tran: 邻居们最终用一根铁撬把门撬开了。

example.ex: Insert the fork about 6in. from the root and simultaneously lever it backwards...
example.tran: 将耙子插入到离根部约6英寸的地方并同时向后扳。

example.ex: Alex levered himself up from the sofa.
example.tran: 亚历克斯从沙发上撑扶着站了起来。

value.def: A lever is an idea or action that you can use to make people do what you want them to do, rather than what they want to do.

example.ex: Radical, militant factions want to continue using the hostages as a lever to gain concessions from the west.
example.tran: 激进的好战派想要继续利用人质作筹码来换取西方的让步。

value.tran: （用作施加压力等的）手段，方法

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to raise, to lighten 提高, 举起；变轻
rootsaffixes.title: lev, liev

partsOfSpeech.dec: al 加强 + levi 提高，举起；变轻 + ate 做，造成，使… → 不断变轻 → 减轻
e 出 + lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ate 做，造成，使… → 举出 → 举起
ir 不 + relevant 相关的 → 不相干的，不切题的
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ee 与…有关的物 → 提高防洪堤的高度来防洪 → 防洪堤
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + el 地点 → 举到同一高度 → 平的
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + er 表物 → 举起〔重物〕的物 → 杠杆
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + it 走 + ate 使… → 举起某物 → 使升到空中
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 变轻 → 轻浮
lev 提高，举起；变轻 + y 表行为 → 提高〔政府收入〕→ 征税
re 一再 + lev 提高，举起；变轻 + ant …的 → 一再想提高的 →〔态度〕中肯的
re 一再 + lief〔= liev〕提高，举起；变轻 → 减轻；轻松
re 一再 + liev 提高，举起；变轻 + e → 使再三变轻 → 减轻
